{
  "texts": [
    "Such subtle attacks tailored to remain below the detection threshold are difficult to detect (refer to Section 8 for possible remedial steps).",
    "Detector limitationsOur core detection solution (see Section 3) is limited to its nnactuators, for any given sensor.",
    "This is not necessarily true when the sensor-actuators(s) relationship are available from the system design document, or when a system expert is able to deduce those relationships.",
    "In our work, we assumed such additional information is unavailable.We mapped a smaller state-space of actuator states to the sensor reading.",
    "As a result, we forsook the determination of a larger number of tighter individual bounds that takes exponential time for the convenience of a practically smaller solution seek space."
  ]
}